... in this case it is the movie itself and not the story. There are a number of problems with this film. First, the acting is atrocious. The main character is played by an unknown actor who seems to be very good at portraying actors that are not familiar with his or her profession (e.g. Robert Mitchum). Secondly, some of the situations are rather clichéd. For instance, there's a scene where a bunch of people run into each other in the middle of nowhere. This is so cliché that it makes no sense whatsoever. Finally, we find out that one of them is a woman. I don't know if this is supposed to have any bearing on the plot but it does.
